channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: At Disastrous G7 Presser, Biden Gives Garbled Answer on Hunter, Snaps at Reporter
House GOP moves to name US coastal waters after Trump
item.description: A new House GOP-led bill aims to rename the coastal waters immediately surrounding the U.S. as the "Donald John Trump Exclusive Economic Zone."

item.title: Rep. Comer to Newsmax: Next President Must 'Clean House' at DOJ
item.description: America needs a president who will "clean house" at the Department of Justice and ensure the nation's intelligence agencies are trustworthy, Rep. James Comer, R-Ky., told Newsmax on Thursday.

item.title: NEW: As Russian Navy Conducts Drills Off the US Coast, Sen. Cruz Goes Off on Biden's Appeasement of Putin
Dem-backed IVF bill slammed by GOP as broad fails key hurdle in Senate
item.description: The Senate voted against advancing a Democratic-backed legislative package that would have expanded access to in vitro fertilization services.

item.title: Jewish Student Denied Diploma After 'Swatting' Antisemitic Poster
item.description: A Jewish student at the University of California-Irvine, said his diploma was withheld because he damaged a poster that was part of the school's anti-Israel encampment, the Washington Examiner reported.

item.title: G7 Agrees to Confiscate Russian Assets to Fund Reparations For Putin's War in Ukraine
Biden judicial nominee takes heat over recommendation for transgender inmate, answer on sex
item.description: Republicans rip President Biden's judicial nominee, Sarah Netburn, for "political activism from the bench" after recommending a convicted rapist be transferred to a women's prison.

item.title: Trump to House GOP: Speak 'Correctly' on Abortion
item.description: Former President Donald Trump, while meeting with House Republicans Thursday, asked them to speak about abortion "correctly" while embracing exceptions to restrictions on the procedure and stressing that decisions are up to the states.

item.title: So Long, Petrodollar: US-Saudi Arabian Agreement Ends After Fifty Years
New poll reveals Biden's border security move fails to satisfy voters as crisis rages
item.description: President Biden's controversial executive order to limit migrant crossings at the southern border has so far failed to win over a majority of voters, a new poll has found.

item.title: Senate Republicans Block Bill on Women's Right to IVF
item.description: Senate Republicans blocked legislation that would make it a right nationwide for women to access in vitro fertilization and other fertility treatments after Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer forced a vote on the matter Thursday in an effort to drive an election-year...

item.title: Are They Finally Tired of Playing Nice? Senate GOP Says They Will Block Biden Nominees Over Trump Lawfare
'No Juicing Joe': Republican proposes bill in response to Biden's 'decline on full display'
item.description: A Tennessee Republican's No Juicing Joe bill would require the president to alert Congress whenever he's taking drugs that could alter his alertness, judgment or mood.

item.title: Sabato's Crystal Ball Moves 6 Predictions to Favor GOP
item.description: Larry Sabato, Director of the Center for Politics at the University of Virginia, has changed his prediction on six electoral races to favor Republicans.
